    • Uses of Element in io.github.samwright.framework.model

      Subinterfaces of Element in io.github.samwright.framework.model 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  WorkflowContainer
      A WorkflowContainer is an Element that contains one or more Workflow objects.
      Classes in io.github.samwright.framework.model that implement Element 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AbstractElement
      Abstract implementation of Element for elemental processors to extend, which requires a one-to-one mapping of input data to output data (without training necessary).
      class  AbstractWorkflowContainer
      Abstract implementation of WorkflowContainer.
      class  ChooserWorkflowContainer
      A WorkflowContainer where one of its Workflow objects will be chosen for processing data.
      class  Optimiser
      A ChooserWorkflowContainer that statically decides during training which Workflow is best suited to each History object of its incoming Mediator objects.
      class  SplitJoinWorkflowContainer
      A WorkflowContainer that allows for all of its Workflow objects to concurrently process input data, before finally joining them together back into a single Mediator output.
      class  TopWorkflowContainer
      An implementation of TopProcessor.
